1241
01:00:35,094 --> 01:00:38,764
one by one gone,
became the norm.

1242
01:00:40,800 --> 01:00:42,568
He was even working
on religion.

1243
01:00:43,636 --> 01:00:45,171
Didn't like the competition.

1244
01:00:46,672 --> 01:00:49,041
Your institutions
didn't disappear

1245
01:00:49,075 --> 01:00:51,110
because of new
technologies or competition,

1246
01:00:51,677 --> 01:00:55,648
they disappeared because they
threatened his regime.

1247
01:00:56,182 --> 01:00:57,716
He saw them as the enemy.

1248
01:00:58,951 --> 01:01:01,720
You mentioned your parents,
did you have any other family?

1249
01:01:01,754 --> 01:01:03,823
No.
It's one of the reasons

1250
01:01:03,856 --> 01:01:05,257
I was chosen to go
on this mission.

1251
01:01:05,291 --> 01:01:06,992
We knew
I was never coming back.

1252
01:01:07,960 --> 01:01:09,361
What's another one?

1253
01:01:10,296 --> 01:01:12,064
I was drafted into the military

1254
01:01:12,098 --> 01:01:13,332
when I was younger
and trained as a sniper.

1255
01:01:14,066 --> 01:01:15,634
Drafted?

1256
01:01:16,001 --> 01:01:19,138
Yes. He started so many
wars around the world

1257
01:01:19,171 --> 01:01:20,873
that the draft
had to be reinstated.

1258
01:01:21,707 --> 01:01:22,942
After his re-election,

1259
01:01:22,975 --> 01:01:24,844
your world never
saw peace again.

1260
01:01:27,079 --> 01:01:28,380
Now you have a chance at it.

1261
01:01:30,749 --> 01:01:32,852
When you decided to go
on this mission

1262
01:01:33,252 --> 01:01:35,321
and knew you couldn't return,
did you think about

1263
01:01:35,354 --> 01:01:37,690
what might happen to you
if you were successful?

1264
01:01:37,723 --> 01:01:38,924
Yes.

1265
01:01:40,092 --> 01:01:42,728
We knew I'd either be caught
or killed in the process.

1266
01:01:42,761 --> 01:01:44,163
And if you were caught,

1267
01:01:44,196 --> 01:01:45,898
what did you think
would happen to you?

1268
01:01:47,366 --> 01:01:48,701
I'd be terminated.

1269
01:01:49,835 --> 01:01:53,739
So knowing you couldn't return
and you most likely die,

1270
01:01:53,973 --> 01:01:55,374
you still chose to do this?

1271
01:01:56,175 --> 01:01:57,810
- Yes.
- Why?

1272
01:01:57,843 --> 01:01:59,178
We had no choice.

1273
01:01:59,211 --> 01:02:01,080
It was a suicide mission.

1274
01:02:01,113 --> 01:02:02,181
Yes.

1275
01:02:03,349 --> 01:02:04,917
Do you want to die?

1276
01:02:05,951 --> 01:02:07,019
No.

1277
01:02:08,187 --> 01:02:10,422
Do you have a terminal illness?

1278
01:02:10,457 --> 01:02:11,657
No.

1279
01:02:12,324 --> 01:02:14,093
Our world was terminal.

1280
01:02:15,060 --> 01:02:16,729
I was the best option.

1281
01:02:19,398 --> 01:02:22,034
Do you truly think
you've saved the world?

1282
01:02:23,402 --> 01:02:24,837
No.

1283
01:02:25,204 --> 01:02:28,307
I made a course correction,
a reboot.

1284
01:02:29,175 --> 01:02:32,111
You were on a different
path before he was elected.

1285
01:02:32,912 --> 01:02:34,481
Now you have a chance
to get there.

