01:02:34,514 --> 01:02:36,081
It doesn't mean you will.

1287
01:02:36,449 --> 01:02:40,085
What happens next is up to you
and the rest of the world.

1288
01:02:40,953 --> 01:02:43,889
What do you mean by a
different path that we were on?

1289
01:02:43,923 --> 01:02:46,158
There was worldwide cooperation

1290
01:02:46,192 --> 01:02:48,727
on protecting the planet
from climate change.

1291
01:02:49,395 --> 01:02:52,465
We're hoping we're not too late
and that that's still possible.

1292
01:02:53,766 --> 01:02:55,100
I bet my life on it.

1293
01:02:56,068 --> 01:02:58,471
There was a global economy

1294
01:02:58,505 --> 01:03:01,974
where countries were
reliant on one another

1295
01:03:02,007 --> 01:03:04,043
and cooperated
and created new industries

1296
01:03:04,076 --> 01:03:06,278
where growth was
ongoing and sustainable.

1297
01:03:06,312 --> 01:03:08,013
Renewable energy was poised

1298
01:03:08,047 --> 01:03:10,049
to become the next
industrial revolution.

1299
01:03:10,916 --> 01:03:12,785
That can happen now.

1300
01:03:13,919 --> 01:03:17,923
Countries around
the world embraced science

1301
01:03:17,957 --> 01:03:20,226
and worked together
to maintain peace,

1302
01:03:20,259 --> 01:03:25,030
to fight tyrants, to fight
terrorists, to fight injustice.

1303
01:03:25,898 --> 01:03:27,933
That's an entirely
different path

1304
01:03:27,967 --> 01:03:30,102
from the one you've been
on since he was elected.

1305
01:03:31,904 --> 01:03:33,372
I hope you succeed.

1306
01:03:35,274 --> 01:03:36,942
My world depends on it.

1307
01:03:42,414 --> 01:03:44,984
I think that may be
a good place to stop.

1308
01:03:46,085 --> 01:03:48,187
Is there anything else
you want to tell the jury?

1309
01:03:50,490 --> 01:03:51,824
Yes.

1310
01:03:52,157 --> 01:03:54,461
[inhaling and exhaling deeply]

1311
01:03:54,494 --> 01:03:56,195
One week from today,

1312
01:03:56,228 --> 01:03:58,330
there will be an
earthquake in Bangkok,

1313
01:03:58,364 --> 01:04:02,067
8,428 people will die.

1314
01:04:02,101 --> 01:04:03,902
Temperature in Duluth,
Minnesota

1315
01:04:03,936 --> 01:04:05,904
will be a high of
73 degrees and a low of 65.

1316
01:04:05,938 --> 01:04:08,274
And the tide
will crest at sunrise

1317
01:04:08,307 --> 01:04:10,209
at four feet in Rio de Janeiro.

1318
01:04:10,242 --> 01:04:11,143
Objection.
That is blatant conjecture.

1319
01:04:11,176 --> 01:04:12,845
Sustained.

1320
01:04:12,878 --> 01:04:14,880
Jurors,
you are to disregard

1321
01:04:14,913 --> 01:04:16,449
that last statement
from the defendant.

1322
01:04:16,483 --> 01:04:18,451
Please strike the
testimony from the record.

1323
01:04:19,318 --> 01:04:21,186
Please proceed, Mr. Johnson.

1324
01:04:21,220 --> 01:04:23,956
Your Honor, we're done with
our testimony for today.

1325
01:04:23,989 --> 01:04:26,593
I'd like to reserve the right
to question my client again.

1326
01:04:26,626 --> 01:04:29,028
Duly noted.
Take your seat, please.

1327
01:04:30,195 --> 01:04:32,398
[chains clanging]

1328
01:04:34,266 --> 01:04:36,835
Okay, then I think
we'll call it a day and begin

1329
01:04:36,869 --> 01:04:38,404
cross-examination
tomorrow morning.

1330
01:04:38,438 --> 01:04:40,540
- Is that okay with you?
- Yes. Your Honor.

1331
01:04:40,573 --> 01:04:42,274
We're ready
whenever you wish.

1332
01:04:42,308 --> 01:04:43,510
Very well then.

1333
01:04:43,543 --> 01:04:45,177
I'd like to remind the jury

1334
01:04:45,210 --> 01:04:46,345
that they've been
sequestered for a reason.

1335
01:04:47,447 --> 01:04:49,549
You're not allowed to watch TV,
read the newspaper,

1336
01:04:49,582 --> 01:04:51,618
or expose yourselves
in any way to coverage

1337
01:04:51,651 --> 01:04:53,385
of this trial
via the media,

1338
01:04:53,419 --> 01:04:55,354
social media,
or through your relationships.

1339
01:04:55,622 --> 01:04:58,090
We'll reconvene at
9:00 AM tomorrow morning.

1340
01:04:58,123 --> 01:05:01,160
[dramatic music playing]

1341
01:05:07,500 --> 01:05:10,437
[papers shuffling]

1342
01:05:12,037 --> 01:05:13,939
Gordon Nicholson
doesn't check out.

1343
01:05:13,972 --> 01:05:16,008
Nothing checks out
about this guy.

1344
01:05:16,041 --> 01:05:18,077
- That was something.
- Yeah.

1345
01:05:18,611 --> 01:05:20,379
I couldn't get a
handle on the jury.

1346
01:05:20,412 --> 01:05:22,081
No kidding.

1347
01:05:22,114 --> 01:05:23,882
Well, do you think
he's telling the truth?

1348
01:05:24,517 --> 01:05:26,251
You know,
whatever he's telling,

1349
01:05:26,285 --> 01:05:28,020
he sure seems
to believe it, so.

1350
01:05:28,053 --> 01:05:30,322
Or he puts
Charles Manson to shame.

1351
01:05:30,356 --> 01:05:31,957
That's what I'm afraid of.

1352
01:05:33,158 --> 01:05:36,228
Or maybe he's just
that good of an actor.

1353
01:05:37,564 --> 01:05:39,365
Well, John Wilkes Booth
was pretty good.

1354
01:05:40,600 --> 01:05:42,067
Did you send her the testimony?

1355
01:05:42,101 --> 01:05:43,503
Yes.

1356
01:05:59,385 --> 01:06:02,421
[exhaling deeply]

1357
01:06:10,095 --> 01:06:13,966
[brooding pensive music]

1358
01:07:04,751 --> 01:07:07,986
[dramatic melancholic playing]

1359
01:08:01,608 --> 01:08:02,775
Have a seat.

1360
01:08:15,488 --> 01:08:17,256
I wanted to talk to you

1361
01:08:17,289 --> 01:08:19,191
about Bradley's
cross-examination today.

1362
01:08:19,692 --> 01:08:21,159
Looking forward to it.

1363
01:08:21,193 --> 01:08:23,463
Yeah. Bet you are.

1364
01:08:24,229 --> 01:08:26,231
But I wanted to talk about
something else first.

1365
01:08:26,666 --> 01:08:28,233
Shoot.

1366
01:08:28,267 --> 01:08:30,302
What was your
father's first name?

1367
01:08:34,641 --> 01:08:35,808
George.

1368
01:08:39,445 --> 01:08:41,213
Are you sure?

1369
01:08:41,246 --> 01:08:43,550
Pretty sure
I know my father's name.

1370
01:08:46,519 --> 01:08:50,790
Just so you know,
my parents are off-limits.

1371
01:08:50,823 --> 01:08:52,825
Their lives cannot
be interfered with.

1372
01:08:52,859 --> 01:08:54,627
It could change
the course of history.

1373
01:08:54,661 --> 01:08:56,629
They need to live their lives

1374
01:08:56,663 --> 01:09:02,100
normally wherever they are
or else I might not be born.

1375
01:09:02,835 --> 01:09:07,172
I could disappear
right in front of your eyes.

1376
01:09:09,876 --> 01:09:11,778
That might be a good thing.

1377
01:09:13,580 --> 01:09:15,147
I'd rather not find out.

1378
01:09:16,381 --> 01:09:18,618
And your country
would rather not find out.

1379
01:09:19,351 --> 01:09:21,788
Please, forget about them.

1380
01:09:23,322 --> 01:09:24,624
And you really believe that?

1381
01:09:24,657 --> 01:09:25,825
Don't you?

1382
01:09:27,225 --> 01:09:28,360
Don't you?

1383
01:09:30,597 --> 01:09:32,565
I don't know what to believe.

1384
01:09:33,499 --> 01:09:36,234
Good.
The jury won't either.

1385
01:09:40,440 --> 01:09:42,341
Leave my parents alone.

1386
01:09:54,186 --> 01:09:57,289
[crowd yelling]

1387
01:10:06,566 --> 01:10:09,267
All they need
is one X-Files fan.

1388
01:10:10,235 --> 01:10:13,138
Didn't think about that
during jury selection.

1389
01:10:13,539 --> 01:10:14,607
[clearing throat]

1390
01:10:16,476 --> 01:10:18,811
I think you better start
thinking about a plea deal.

1391
01:10:19,612 --> 01:10:21,648
Do you want to take the
death penalty off the table?

1392
01:10:22,280 --> 01:10:23,816
I think you better
start thinking

1393
01:10:23,850 --> 01:10:25,317
about getting disbarred.

1394
01:10:25,350 --> 01:10:27,219
We're gonna fry his ass.

1395
01:10:27,520 --> 01:10:28,888
You think he's insane,
don't you?

1396
01:10:29,822 --> 01:10:31,591
And if you think he's crazy,

1397
01:10:31,624 --> 01:10:33,593
what do you think
the jury thinks?

1398
01:10:33,993 --> 01:10:35,695
I don't think he's crazy.

1399
01:10:35,728 --> 01:10:37,262
You must be though.

1400
01:10:37,664 --> 01:10:39,532
He's just a liar and a con.

1401
01:10:40,232 --> 01:10:41,434
Believe what you want.

1402
01:10:42,367 --> 01:10:44,302
You're sure you want
to take that chance?

1403
01:10:45,738 --> 01:10:47,940
All I need is one
Trekkie on the jury.

1404
01:10:48,574 --> 01:10:50,510
All I need is
one lie out of you

1405
01:10:50,543 --> 01:10:52,478
and you can kiss
your license goodbye.

1406
01:10:52,512 --> 01:10:54,547
Your client is all mine today.

1407
01:10:57,016 --> 01:10:58,718
Just think about it.

1408
01:11:04,322 --> 01:11:07,760
[chains clanging]

1409
01:11:17,970 --> 01:11:19,772
All rise.

1410
01:11:24,844 --> 01:11:25,945
You may be seated.

1411
01:11:27,647 --> 01:11:29,749
Hope everyone
had a relaxing evening.

1412
01:11:29,782 --> 01:11:30,950
I believe it's your turn,
Mr. Bradley.

1413
01:11:30,983 --> 01:11:32,485
Thank you, Your Honor.

1414
01:11:32,518 --> 01:11:33,886
I'd like to recall
the defendant,

1415
01:11:33,920 --> 01:11:35,387
John Doe to the stand.

1416
01:11:35,420 --> 01:11:36,789
Mr. Doe, please be seated.

1417
01:11:49,769 --> 01:11:51,269
You are still
sworn in from yesterday.

1418
01:11:51,303 --> 01:11:52,605
Do you understand?

1419
01:11:52,638 --> 01:11:53,773
Yes, Your Honor.

1420
01:11:56,943 --> 01:11:58,911
Now, before we get started,

1421
01:11:58,945 --> 01:12:02,482
I just have to say that your
testimony so far has just been

1422
01:12:02,515 --> 01:12:06,384
the wildest charade
that I have ever experienced.

1423
01:12:06,719 --> 01:12:08,888
Wow, oh, wow.

1424
01:12:08,921 --> 01:12:11,691
You can really tell a story.

1425
01:12:11,724 --> 01:12:15,628
I mean, [chuckling]
corporate pilot, Navy SEAL.

1426
01:12:15,661 --> 01:12:19,031
Oh, and my favorite Future Man.

1427
01:12:19,065 --> 01:12:21,467
So congratulations on that.

1428
01:12:21,501 --> 01:12:23,603
Just amazing.

1429
01:12:23,636 --> 01:12:28,306
Now, Mr. Doe,
or is it Mr. Nicholson,

1430
01:12:28,340 --> 01:12:29,909
or... or maybe you'd like
to be somebody else today.

1431
01:12:29,942 --> 01:12:31,844
What would you like me
to call you?

1432
01:12:31,878 --> 01:12:33,579
My name is Gordon Nicholson.

1433
01:12:33,613 --> 01:12:36,381
You may call me whatever
you like, Mr. Bradley.

1434
01:12:36,414 --> 01:12:39,351
Well, we did a background
check on Gordon Nicholson

1435
01:12:39,384 --> 01:12:41,821
and I have to tell you,
none of the Gordon Nicholsons

1436
01:12:41,854 --> 01:12:44,457
we could find seemed
to match up with you.

1437
01:12:44,490 --> 01:12:46,058
Why do you think that is?

1438
01:12:46,092 --> 01:12:47,527
Objection.
Leading the witness.

1439
01:12:47,894 --> 01:12:49,427
I'll rephrase that, Your Honor.

1440
01:12:49,996 --> 01:12:51,898
Do you realize you're
committing perjury

1441
01:12:51,931 --> 01:12:53,432
with your testimony
in this court?

1442
01:12:53,866 --> 01:12:55,067
I'm telling the truth.

1443
01:12:55,635 --> 01:12:57,335
You just don't want to hear it.

1444
01:12:57,369 --> 01:12:58,738
I'll tell you
what I want to hear.

1445
01:12:59,071 --> 01:13:01,040
Why did you make up
another name for yourself?

1446
01:13:01,073 --> 01:13:02,642
What are you trying to hide?

1447
01:13:03,009 --> 01:13:06,879
There are no records on me
because I haven't been born.

1448
01:13:06,913 --> 01:13:11,050
Oh, right.
Future Man, the time traveler.

1449
01:13:11,083 --> 01:13:12,985
Well, Future Man,

1450
01:13:13,686 --> 01:13:15,655
who's going to win
the lottery tomorrow?

1451
01:13:15,688 --> 01:13:17,422
I don't know.

1452
01:13:17,456 --> 01:13:20,026
Don't know.
Well, wh... why don't you know?

1453
01:13:20,059 --> 01:13:21,594
I thought you could
predict the future?

1454
01:13:21,627 --> 01:13:22,995
I'm not a psychic.

1455
01:13:23,029 --> 01:13:24,463
I'm a historian.

1456
01:13:24,497 --> 01:13:25,798
A historian.

1457
01:13:25,832 --> 01:13:27,767
Terrific.
Let me get this straight.

1458
01:13:27,800 --> 01:13:31,871
A corporate pilot,
Navy SEAL, and historian.

1459
01:13:31,904 --> 01:13:34,540
Yes. Oh, and let's not
forget the big one,

1460
01:13:35,074 --> 01:13:38,010
time traveler
sent to save us all.

1461
01:13:38,678 --> 01:13:40,746
Well, Mr. Time Traveler,

1462
01:13:41,180 --> 01:13:43,983
tell me, do you own
a flux capacitor?

1463
01:13:44,984 --> 01:13:47,720
What's a flux capacitor?

1464
01:13:47,753 --> 01:13:49,589
How about a DeLorean.

1465
01:13:50,723 --> 01:13:52,124
I don't understand
the question.

1466
01:13:52,158 --> 01:13:54,861
Haven't you seen
Back to the Future?

1467
01:13:55,628 --> 01:13:57,163
Is it a movie?

1468
01:13:57,196 --> 01:14:01,000
Yes. About returning
from the future,

1469
01:14:01,033 --> 01:14:03,903
and the flux capacitor
was absolutely critical

1470
01:14:03,936 --> 01:14:05,972
to their ability to
travel through time.

1471
01:14:06,005 --> 01:14:09,175
So you mean to say that
you've traveled through time

1472
01:14:09,208 --> 01:14:12,011
and you don't know
what a flux capacitor is?

1473
01:14:12,044 --> 01:14:14,046
What kind of
time traveler are you?

1474
01:14:14,881 --> 01:14:16,616
A successful one.

1475
01:14:16,649 --> 01:14:19,518
No. An imaginary one,

1476
01:14:19,552 --> 01:14:21,153
just like the movie.

1477
01:14:21,187 --> 01:14:23,856
I'll grant you.
You have quite an imagination.

1478
01:14:23,890 --> 01:14:25,691
You could've had a
future in Hollywood

1479
01:14:25,725 --> 01:14:28,194
making up grandiose
science fiction stories.

1480
01:14:28,227 --> 01:14:30,930
It's too bad you
chose to assassinate

1481
01:14:30,963 --> 01:14:33,933
the President of the
United States instead.

1482
01:14:33,966 --> 01:14:36,035
It's too bad.
You chose to be

1483
01:14:36,068 --> 01:14:38,804
Lee Harvey Oswald instead
of Steven Spielberg.

1484
01:14:38,838 --> 01:14:41,140
Oswald was from the future.

1485
01:14:41,173 --> 01:14:43,009
Oswald was from the future.

1486
01:14:43,042 --> 01:14:44,510
Of course.

1487
01:14:44,543 --> 01:14:46,045
Why didn't anyone
think of that?

1488
01:14:46,779 --> 01:14:48,147
They didn't get the chance.

1489
01:14:48,180 --> 01:14:49,916
There was never a trial.

1490
01:14:49,949 --> 01:14:52,451
Did Oswald have
a flux capacitor?

1491
01:14:52,485 --> 01:14:55,655
No, he used the prototype
of the machine I used.

1492
01:14:55,688 --> 01:14:56,923
Your Honor,
how much of this lunacy

1493
01:14:56,956 --> 01:14:58,557
do we have
to put up with?

1494
01:14:58,591 --> 01:15:00,593
Are you suggesting
my client is crazy?

1495
01:15:00,626 --> 01:15:03,129
Yes.
Are you suggesting something?

1496
01:15:03,162 --> 01:15:04,997
No, Your Honor.

1497
01:15:05,031 --> 01:15:06,565
Then proceed.

1498
01:15:06,599 --> 01:15:08,901
Okay. Love to.

1499
01:15:08,935 --> 01:15:10,770
I think
we've given Mr. Doe here

1500
01:15:10,803 --> 01:15:12,939
ample time for his
flights of fancy.

1501
01:15:12,972 --> 01:15:14,807
I'd like to move on.

1502
01:15:14,840 --> 01:15:17,576
Mr. Doe
or how about Marty McFly,

1503
01:15:17,610 --> 01:15:18,978
[crowd giggling]

1504
01:15:19,011 --> 01:15:21,147
how did you feel
about our president?

1505
01:15:21,180 --> 01:15:23,716
- I didn't know him.
- Did you hate him?

1506
01:15:23,749 --> 01:15:25,918
I didn't have
any feelings for him.

1507
01:15:25,952 --> 01:15:27,853
Why did you kill him?

1508
01:15:27,887 --> 01:15:30,690
His actions would destroy me
and the rest of the world.

1509
01:15:30,723 --> 01:15:32,591
Oh, yeah, I forgot.

1510
01:15:32,625 --> 01:15:34,694
You were on a mission

1511
01:15:34,727 --> 01:15:36,796
- with clear intent, yes?
- Yes.

1512
01:15:36,829 --> 01:15:39,932
Would you say that your intent
was to destroy this country?

1513
01:15:39,966 --> 01:15:41,600
No, the opposite.

1514
01:15:41,634 --> 01:15:43,636
Are you aware that
there are riots happening

1515
01:15:43,669 --> 01:15:45,204
in the street as we speak?

1516
01:15:45,237 --> 01:15:47,840
Are you aware that this
country is coming apart?

1517
01:15:47,873 --> 01:15:49,275
Was that your intent?

1518
01:15:49,308 --> 01:15:51,077
No, but we knew there would be

1519
01:15:51,110 --> 01:15:54,814
a high probability rate
for internal strife.

1520
01:15:54,847 --> 01:15:57,883
Internal strife.

1521
01:15:57,917 --> 01:16:01,687
People are dying every day in
the streets because of you.

1522
01:16:01,721 --> 01:16:03,889
This is not some fantasy world.

1523
01:16:03,923 --> 01:16:05,124
This is real.

1524
01:16:06,058 --> 01:16:08,661
So that was not your intent?

1525
01:16:09,829 --> 01:16:10,896
Correct.

1526
01:16:10,930 --> 01:16:12,131
But you had clear intent. Yes?

1527
01:16:12,164 --> 01:16:13,299
Yes.

1528
01:16:13,332 --> 01:16:15,935
- To save the world.
- Yes.

1529
01:16:15,968 --> 01:16:18,237
You knew this could happen
and you did it anyway.

1530
01:16:18,270 --> 01:16:21,273
You survived a civil war.
You'll survive this.

1531
01:16:21,307 --> 01:16:23,309
Oh, yeah, Future Man again.

1532
01:16:23,342 --> 01:16:25,244
Well, Future Man,

1533
01:16:25,277 --> 01:16:26,879
you're not just an assassin.

1534
01:16:26,912 --> 01:16:29,115
You're a terrorist.

1535
01:16:29,148 --> 01:16:31,217
- Objection.
- Overruled.

1536
01:16:31,250 --> 01:16:32,885
Fits the definition.

1537
01:16:34,620 --> 01:16:36,622
Do you remember
the video we played?

1538
01:16:36,655 --> 01:16:37,723
Yes.

1539
01:16:37,757 --> 01:16:39,125
Was that you in the video?

1540
01:16:39,158 --> 01:16:40,292
It looked like me.

1541
01:16:40,326 --> 01:16:42,128
- But was it you?
- Yes.

1542
01:16:42,161 --> 01:16:44,330
So you don't deny
killing the president?

1543
01:16:44,363 --> 01:16:45,931
I would not deny that, no.

1544
01:16:45,965 --> 01:16:47,900
Did you kill the president?

1545
01:16:47,933 --> 01:16:49,301
- Yes.
- Why?

1546
01:16:49,335 --> 01:16:52,638
I told you,
to protect the world.

1547
01:16:52,671 --> 01:16:54,306
You believe
he had to be stopped?

1548
01:16:54,340 --> 01:16:55,641
Yes.

1549
01:16:55,674 --> 01:16:58,077
So you purchased
a sniper rifle,

1550
01:16:58,110 --> 01:17:00,079
rented an apartment,
and then waited for the

1551
01:17:00,112 --> 01:17:01,614
president to go
to one of his rallies?

1552
01:17:01,647 --> 01:17:03,716
- Objection.
- I'll rephrase that.

1553
01:17:03,749 --> 01:17:06,352
Did you purchase a sniper
rifle, rent an apartment,

1554
01:17:06,385 --> 01:17:08,687
and wait for the president
to go to one of his rallies?

1555
01:17:08,721 --> 01:17:09,822
Yes.

1556
01:17:09,855 --> 01:17:11,190
Did you shoot the president

1557
01:17:11,223 --> 01:17:13,359
and Agent Winslow
with intent to kill?

1558
01:17:13,392 --> 01:17:15,227
Not Agent Winslow.

1559
01:17:15,261 --> 01:17:17,229
He was innocent, but I had
to shoot him in the leg

1560
01:17:17,263 --> 01:17:19,098
to give me a clear shot
on the president.

1561
01:17:19,131 --> 01:17:21,167
Did you shoot the president
with intent to kill him?

1562
01:17:21,200 --> 01:17:22,101
Yes.

1563
01:17:22,868 --> 01:17:24,670
Thank you.

1564
01:17:24,703 --> 01:17:26,972
Please note that
the defendant has just

1565
01:17:27,006 --> 01:17:29,341
admitted to
planning out his attack

1566
01:17:29,375 --> 01:17:32,078
and to shooting the
president with intent to kill.

1567
01:17:32,111 --> 01:17:36,916
All insanity pleas are based on
the intent to commit the crime.

1568
01:17:37,950 --> 01:17:39,852
We've just met
our burden of proof.

1569
01:17:40,653 --> 01:17:42,088
Congratulations.

1570
01:17:43,722 --> 01:17:45,791
We have no further questions,
Your Honor.

1571
01:17:46,158 --> 01:17:48,260
Very well. Mr. Johnson?

1572
01:17:48,294 --> 01:17:49,862
Redirect, Your Honor.

1573
01:17:49,895 --> 01:17:51,263
Thank you, Mr. Bradley.

1574
01:17:56,735 --> 01:17:58,938
Okay. I'm confused.

1575
01:17:58,971 --> 01:18:00,906
When Mr. Bradley was asking
his questions,

1576
01:18:00,940 --> 01:18:03,976
you mentioned that Lee Harvey
Oswald was from the future.

1577
01:18:04,009 --> 01:18:05,111
Yes.

1578
01:18:05,911 --> 01:18:07,413
That doesn't make sense to me.

1579
01:18:07,447 --> 01:18:09,782
John F. Kennedy was revered.

1580
01:18:09,815 --> 01:18:11,650
Why would someone from the
future want

1581
01:18:11,684 --> 01:18:13,853
to assassinate one of our most
respected presidents?

1582
01:18:13,886 --> 01:18:16,088
[Bradley] Objection.
Relevancy, Your Honor.

1583
01:18:16,122 --> 01:18:18,224
The subject was introduced
under Mr. Bradley's cross.

1584
01:18:18,257 --> 01:18:19,925
It was relevant then.

1585
01:18:19,959 --> 01:18:22,328
Overruled. You may proceed.

1586
01:18:22,361 --> 01:18:24,830
Okay. Again, why would
someone from the future

1587
01:18:24,864 --> 01:18:26,999
want to assassinate
President Kennedy?

1588
01:18:27,032 --> 01:18:29,135
To save the world from
destruction.

1589
01:18:29,168 --> 01:18:31,270
I don't understand.

1590
01:18:31,303 --> 01:18:34,206
Kennedy would have gone back to
Washington after Dallas.

1591
01:18:34,240 --> 01:18:36,041
News of his affairs
would leak out.

1592
01:18:36,075 --> 01:18:38,344
Marilyn Monroe
had been carrying his child.

1593
01:18:38,377 --> 01:18:40,379
Jackie found out and left him.

1594
01:18:40,412 --> 01:18:42,781
He was wounded politically and
didn't have the moral authority

1595
01:18:42,815 --> 01:18:45,317
to get his civil rights agenda
through Congress.

1596
01:18:45,351 --> 01:18:47,920
The next 20 years of racial
progress never happened.

1597
01:18:47,953 --> 01:18:50,055
No Obama.

1598
01:18:50,089 --> 01:18:52,758
Barry Goldwater won the
Republican primary and went on

1599
01:18:52,791 --> 01:18:56,962
to trounce Kennedy in the 1964
presidential election.

1600
01:18:56,996 --> 01:18:58,831
The day Goldwater was sworn in,

1601
01:18:58,864 --> 01:19:03,335
he dropped a bomb... a nuclear
bomb on North Vietnam.

1602
01:19:04,270 --> 01:19:05,871
China didn't like that.

1603
01:19:05,905 --> 01:19:08,307
They got involved
and Russia, Europe.

1604
01:19:08,340 --> 01:19:10,142
We were on the brink of
destruction.

1605
01:19:11,777 --> 01:19:15,448
When Oswald shot Kennedy,
the country mourned.

1606
01:19:15,482 --> 01:19:18,984
His assassination made Kennedy
a tragic hero.

1607
01:19:20,252 --> 01:19:22,721
It gave Johnson the moral
authority

1608
01:19:22,755 --> 01:19:25,224
to get Kennedy's civil rights
agenda through Congress,

1609
01:19:25,257 --> 01:19:29,295
and as destructive as the
Vietnam War became,

1610
01:19:31,397 --> 01:19:33,466
nuclear war was averted.

1611
01:19:33,500 --> 01:19:35,734
The world was saved until now.

1612
01:19:37,970 --> 01:19:39,338
So now it's your turn?

1613
01:19:39,371 --> 01:19:40,440
[Amos] Yes.

1614
01:19:42,007 --> 01:19:44,176
Do you really believe
you're from the future?

1615
01:19:44,210 --> 01:19:45,277
Yes.

1616
01:19:46,378 --> 01:19:48,781
So what you had to do,

1617
01:19:48,814 --> 01:19:50,883
you had to do?

1618
01:19:50,916 --> 01:19:52,051
Yes.

1619
01:19:53,419 --> 01:19:55,287
Would you agree to take
a polygraph test?

1620
01:19:55,321 --> 01:19:56,523
Yes.

1621
01:19:56,556 --> 01:19:57,990
- [Jason] DNA test?
- Yes.

1622
01:19:59,291 --> 01:20:01,293
Want to take him up on it?

1623
01:20:01,327 --> 01:20:02,962
[Bradley] We have
a ballistics test.

1624
01:20:02,995 --> 01:20:05,030
Thank you.

1625
01:20:05,064 --> 01:20:06,265
Very well.

1626
01:20:07,500 --> 01:20:09,502
We're done with our testimony,
Your Honor.

1627
01:20:11,103 --> 01:20:12,338
Recross, Your Honor.

1628
01:20:12,371 --> 01:20:13,939
[Judge] Mr. Bradley.

1629
01:20:15,575 --> 01:20:18,277
Well, that was quite a yarn.

1630
01:20:18,310 --> 01:20:20,012
Did you just make that up

1631
01:20:20,045 --> 01:20:22,047
or had you thought it all out
ahead of time?

1632
01:20:22,081 --> 01:20:23,949
Ahead of time,
40 years from now.

1633
01:20:23,983 --> 01:20:27,186
Well, what about that wild
story you told your landlord

1634
01:20:27,219 --> 01:20:29,154
about being an airline pilot?

1635
01:20:29,188 --> 01:20:30,956
Was that the truth,

1636
01:20:30,990 --> 01:20:33,225
or had you thought that all up
40 years from now?

1637
01:20:33,259 --> 01:20:35,462
No, Mr. Doe.

1638
01:20:35,495 --> 01:20:37,096
I think you've got

1639
01:20:37,129 --> 01:20:38,964
a pathological aversion
to the truth.

1640
01:20:39,599 --> 01:20:41,900
I think you like to tell lies

1641
01:20:41,934 --> 01:20:44,136
because in every
story you have told,

1642
01:20:44,169 --> 01:20:47,440
you have not offered
one scintilla of proof.

1643
01:20:48,140 --> 01:20:49,975
Nothing.

1644
01:20:50,009 --> 01:20:53,078
Your entire testimony has
been a fabrication, hasn't it?

1645
01:20:53,112 --> 01:20:55,482
No. I can prove it.

1646
01:20:56,348 --> 01:20:59,118
- You can?
- Yes. It's simple.

1647
01:20:59,151 --> 01:21:01,253
How did Oswald know
to get a job

1648
01:21:01,287 --> 01:21:02,988
at the Texas School
Book Depository

1649
01:21:03,022 --> 01:21:06,091
over a month ahead of
Kennedy's trip to Dallas?

1650
01:21:07,026 --> 01:21:09,496
With all of the jobs
available in Dallas,

1651
01:21:09,529 --> 01:21:12,197
why did he decide to look
for a place to work

1652
01:21:12,231 --> 01:21:14,366
with the perfect view
of Kennedy's route

1653
01:21:14,400 --> 01:21:17,269
before anyone knew Kennedy was
going to be there,

1654
01:21:17,303 --> 01:21:19,572
let alone
what his route would be?

1655
01:21:19,606 --> 01:21:22,241
Excuse me. I'm the one
asking the questions.

1656
01:21:22,274 --> 01:21:24,877
They didn't even decide on
his route until the day before.

1657
01:21:24,910 --> 01:21:26,412
[Bradley] That's enough.

1658
01:21:26,446 --> 01:21:29,081
How did he know ahead
of time to be right there

1659
01:21:29,114 --> 01:21:31,250
in that location on that day?

1660
01:21:31,283 --> 01:21:32,985
- Your Honor.
- That's enough.

1661
01:21:33,018 --> 01:21:35,988
You've investigated
for over half a century

1662
01:21:36,021 --> 01:21:38,558
and theorized about
Kennedy's assassination

1663
01:21:38,591 --> 01:21:40,426
when you've ignored the
evidence that's been staring

1664
01:21:40,460 --> 01:21:42,027
you in the face
the entire time?

1665
01:21:42,061 --> 01:21:43,630
- Now!
- How did he know to be there?

1666
01:21:43,663 --> 01:21:45,230
Who cares?

1667
01:21:45,264 --> 01:21:46,566
That was then.

1668
01:21:46,599 --> 01:21:48,535
We're dealing with the here
and now.

1669
01:21:48,568 --> 01:21:51,170
The here and now where
you assassinated

1670
01:21:51,203 --> 01:21:53,540
the President of
the United States,

1671
01:21:53,573 --> 01:21:55,575
not Lee Harvey Oswald, you.

1672
01:21:57,042 --> 01:21:59,411
This is not some
alternate universe.

1673
01:21:59,446 --> 01:22:01,180
You didn't beam yourself
into that chair

1674
01:22:01,213 --> 01:22:03,115
and neither did they.

1675
01:22:03,148 --> 01:22:06,519
So how about we forget the
fantasy that you are selling?

1676
01:22:07,986 --> 01:22:12,124
Your entire testimony has
been a complete fabrication.

1677
01:22:13,425 --> 01:22:14,960
How did he know?

1678
01:22:16,195 --> 01:22:18,598
Don't you remember?

1679
01:22:18,631 --> 01:22:21,501
The CIA killed Kennedy.

1680
01:22:21,534 --> 01:22:24,236
Oswald was part of their plan.

1681
01:22:24,269 --> 01:22:25,638
That's how he knew.

1682
01:22:25,672 --> 01:22:27,640
No, wait,
he was with the mafia.

1683
01:22:27,674 --> 01:22:30,209
They killed Kennedy,
or he was an alien,

1684
01:22:30,242 --> 01:22:32,211
or he was a psychic.
No, wait.

1685
01:22:32,244 --> 01:22:33,912
He was playing
with a Ouija board

1686
01:22:33,946 --> 01:22:35,648
and spelled out Book
Depository.

1687
01:22:35,682 --> 01:22:38,585
Do you see how easy this is?

1688
01:22:39,486 --> 01:22:43,222
I'm done with this witness,
Your Honor.

1689
01:22:44,056 --> 01:22:46,258
Okay. Mr. Doe,
please be seated.

1690
01:22:49,094 --> 01:22:52,699
[chains clanging]

1691
01:22:52,732 --> 01:22:54,534
How?

1692
01:23:00,540 --> 01:23:02,040
We have one more witness,
your Honor.

1693
01:23:02,074 --> 01:23:03,643
Objection.

1694
01:23:03,676 --> 01:23:05,277
He hasn't submitted
anyone to the witness list.

1695
01:23:05,310 --> 01:23:07,045
She was one of yours.

1696
01:23:07,079 --> 01:23:09,616
Dr. Amanda Beal,
your mental health expert,

1697
01:23:09,649 --> 01:23:11,283
you filed
her report with the court.

1698
01:23:12,184 --> 01:23:13,952
Very well.

1699
01:23:13,986 --> 01:23:15,988
I'd like to call Dr. Amanda
Beal to the stand.

1700
01:23:29,201 --> 01:23:30,402
What the fuck is this?

1701
01:23:30,437 --> 01:23:32,304
I don't know. Did she call you?

1702
01:23:36,141 --> 01:23:37,943
You are still sworn in,
Dr. Beal.

1703
01:23:41,581 --> 01:23:43,483
Good afternoon, Dr. Beal.

1704
01:23:44,451 --> 01:23:46,519
Some would say you're
the country's leading expert

1705
01:23:46,553 --> 01:23:50,490
on legal issues as they relate
to psychology, is that correct?

1706
01:23:50,523 --> 01:23:52,459
I'm sorry,
I'm... I'm not comfortable

1707
01:23:52,492 --> 01:23:54,993
commenting on speculation
about my credentials.

1708
01:23:55,027 --> 01:23:56,395
Fair enough.

1709
01:23:56,428 --> 01:23:58,263
Would you mind sharing
your credentials?

1710
01:23:58,297 --> 01:24:00,700
I have a PhD
in clinical psychiatry

1711
01:24:00,733 --> 01:24:03,570
and a PhD in criminal justice,
both from Harvard.

1712
01:24:03,603 --> 01:24:05,370
So let's be clear.

1713
01:24:05,404 --> 01:24:07,440
Of all the professionals
in your field

1714
01:24:07,474 --> 01:24:09,208
that the federal government
could pick from

1715
01:24:09,241 --> 01:24:10,777
in the entire country,

1716
01:24:10,810 --> 01:24:12,712
the entire world for that
matter, they picked you?

1717
01:24:12,745 --> 01:24:14,012
Yes.

1718
01:24:15,247 --> 01:24:16,749
Are you the psychiatrist
who determined

1719
01:24:16,783 --> 01:24:19,151
that my client was
competent to stand trial?

1720
01:24:19,184 --> 01:24:21,019
Yes.

1721
01:24:21,053 --> 01:24:23,456
Did you spend any time with
him in forming your opinion?

1722
01:24:23,490 --> 01:24:25,190
Yes, I did.

1723
01:24:25,224 --> 01:24:27,359
I had a couple of sessions
with him actually.

1724
01:24:27,392 --> 01:24:30,062
And your recommendation was
that my client was competent?

1725
01:24:30,095 --> 01:24:31,664
Yes.

1726
01:24:31,698 --> 01:24:34,333
Would you mind sharing
how you reached your decision?

1727
01:24:34,366 --> 01:24:37,704
The test for
competency is simple.

1728
01:24:37,737 --> 01:24:41,106
Uh, the defendant must have
the ability to consult

1729
01:24:41,139 --> 01:24:44,611
with his attorney and have
a rational understanding

1730
01:24:44,644 --> 01:24:46,479
of the proceedings
against him or her.

1731
01:24:46,513 --> 01:24:49,682
- Not a high bar?
- No, but some don't need it.

1732
01:24:50,750 --> 01:24:52,519
And in your sessions,
did my client mention

1733
01:24:52,552 --> 01:24:54,521
that he was from the future?

1734
01:24:54,554 --> 01:24:56,221
No, he did not.

1735
01:24:56,255 --> 01:24:57,624
He shared very little actually.

1736
01:24:58,290 --> 01:25:01,193
You've not been here for
all of the testimony, correct?

1737
01:25:01,226 --> 01:25:03,128
Correct.

1738
01:25:03,161 --> 01:25:04,831
Did you receive the
transcripts that my office

1739
01:25:04,864 --> 01:25:06,633
couriered to you
earlier today?

1740
01:25:06,666 --> 01:25:08,166
Yes, I did.

1741
01:25:08,200 --> 01:25:10,168
- Did you read them?
- Yes.

1742
01:25:10,202 --> 01:25:12,304
Did you see the part where
he said he was from the future?

1743
01:25:12,337 --> 01:25:14,106
I did.

1744
01:25:14,139 --> 01:25:16,442
And that he believes
he was protecting the world?

1745
01:25:17,443 --> 01:25:19,278
Yes.

1746
01:25:19,311 --> 01:25:22,147
What was your expert opinion
when you read his testimony?

1747
01:25:23,483 --> 01:25:26,719
That he could be delusional or
possibly paranoid delusional.

1748
01:25:26,753 --> 01:25:29,254
And what
exactly does that mean?

1749
01:25:29,288 --> 01:25:33,225
It means that he believes
in an alternate reality

1750
01:25:33,258 --> 01:25:36,328
where things or people
are out to get him.

1751
01:25:36,361 --> 01:25:39,197
Could he believe that
he's from the future

1752
01:25:39,231 --> 01:25:42,435
and that his life and
environment were under attack?

1753
01:25:42,468 --> 01:25:44,269
Yes.

1754
01:25:44,303 --> 01:25:47,239
Would he be in control of his
actions in that reality?

1755
01:25:48,541 --> 01:25:51,844
Yes, if his actions
supported his reality.

1756
01:25:51,878 --> 01:25:54,379
- Could he kill?
- Yes.

1757
01:25:54,413 --> 01:25:57,416
- And believe he was justified?
- Yes.

1758
01:25:57,450 --> 01:25:59,619
I'm not delusional.

1759
01:25:59,652 --> 01:26:01,721
What don't
you people understand?

1760
01:26:01,754 --> 01:26:03,489
- [Judge] Mr. Doe.
- I just saved you.

1761
01:26:03,523 --> 01:26:05,491
[Judge] Order.

1762
01:26:05,525 --> 01:26:07,560
Mr. Doe,
or whoever you are,

1763
01:26:07,594 --> 01:26:10,262
I'll have you gagged if you
don't sit down right now.

1764
01:26:10,295 --> 01:26:12,097
I mean that.

1765
01:26:19,939 --> 01:26:20,807
Proceed.

1766
01:26:23,509 --> 01:26:26,679
What are some other things
to watch for?

1767
01:26:28,413 --> 01:26:31,249
Well, uh,
a person can appear normal

1768
01:26:31,283 --> 01:26:34,621
in all other areas
except their delusion.

1769
01:26:34,654 --> 01:26:36,889
[Jason] What do you mean?

1770
01:26:36,923 --> 01:26:40,325
We could be having a normal
conversation and the person

1771
01:26:40,359 --> 01:26:44,396
can say, "The earth is flat,"
and believe it.

1772
01:26:44,429 --> 01:26:46,466
And if someone
suffered from that,

1773
01:26:46,499 --> 01:26:49,334
would they legally be
responsible for their actions?

1774
01:26:49,602 --> 01:26:51,269
No.

1775
01:26:51,303 --> 01:26:54,540
Well, none that are
related to that delusion.

1776
01:26:54,574 --> 01:26:58,544
Um, if you wrecked a car,
for example,

1777
01:26:58,578 --> 01:27:00,613
you would be responsible
for your actions.

1778
01:27:00,647 --> 01:27:03,850
But if you wrecked a car
thinking it was a submarine,

1779
01:27:03,883 --> 01:27:05,618
you wouldn't.

1780
01:27:05,652 --> 01:27:07,285
So to be clear,

1781
01:27:07,319 --> 01:27:10,222
a person can have control
over their actions

1782
01:27:10,255 --> 01:27:12,558
within the delusion,
but they would not be

1783
01:27:12,592 --> 01:27:15,260
legally responsible for those
actions, correct?

1784
01:27:15,293 --> 01:27:17,530
- Correct.
- Thank you.

1785
01:27:18,564 --> 01:27:20,566
Just one last question.

1786
01:27:20,600 --> 01:27:23,469
When you provide expert
testimony for the prosecution,

1787
01:27:23,503 --> 01:27:25,672
are you
paid for your expertise?

1788
01:27:25,705 --> 01:27:26,506
Yes.

1789
01:27:27,339 --> 01:27:29,776
He's your client, not me,
